findings.title: newun address
findings.description: If newun equals zero address and transferFrom function will be called, the address of receiver will be blocked until owner changes newun address. But when the owner is renounced, it will be blocked permanently.

findings.title: Owner can block one user address to receive tokens.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to block a specific user address from receiving tokens.

findings.title: Owner can withdraw BNBs from the contract
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to withdraw BNBs from the contract, which is not considered an issue as it's a sale contract.
